gomodel:SYNGO_4973  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: SRGAP2A and the emergence of the human-specific paralogs SRGAP2B and SRGAP2C.\n\nAuthors analyzed the ability of human-SRGAP2B and -SRGAP2C to regulate excitatory synaptic density and maturation in mice by quantifying spine density and spine head size of apical oblique dendrites at juvenile (P21 - Fig. 3) and adult (>P65 - Fig. 4) stages of layer 2/3 cortical pyramidal neurons.\n\nFigure 3c, 4b: expression of SRGAP2C induced an increase in dendritic spine density at P21 and P65.\n\nFigure 3d, 4c: expression of SRGAP2C induced a decrease in dendritic spine head size at P21 but no significant differences at P65.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n\"Cortical neurons were ex utero electroporated (EUE) by injecting endotoxin-free DNA (500 ng/ul for cell filler and 750 ng/ul for each fusion protein construct) into the lateral ventricle of E15.5 mouse embryos and ...\"\n\n\"Plasmids for expression of SRGAP2A-RFP, SRGAP2C-RFP, SRGAP2B-RFP, F-BARΔ49 -RFP, 5R-RFP, F-BARx-RFP, and myristoylated-Venus (mVenus), were as previously described\" (PMID: 22559944)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4973" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

